Company Description                    




                        Centrais Eletricas Brasileiras S.A., Eletrobras, is a mixed economy company and its capital is traded in Sao Paulo, Madrid and New York Stock Exchanges. The company has been created in 1962 to promote studies and projects for the construction and operation of generating plants, transmission lines and substations, destined to the supplement of the country's electric energy. Eletrobras' companies produce about 60% of the electrical energy consumed in Brazil.                     


